#: ../../../guides/recipes/direnv.md:2
msgid "Automatic environment activation with `direnv`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/direnv.md:4
msgid ""
"Instead of manually activating the environment for each project, you can "
"reload a [declarative shell](declarative-reproducible-envs) every time you "
"enter the project's directory or change the `shell.nix` inside it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/direnv.md:6
msgid ""
"[Make nix-direnv available](https://github.com/nix-community/nix-direnv)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/direnv.md:7
msgid "[Hook it into your shell](https://direnv.net/docs/hook.html)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/direnv.md:9
msgid "For example, write a `shell.nix` with the following contents:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/direnv.md:11
msgid ""
"let\n"
"  nixpkgs = fetchTarball \"https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/tarball/"
"nixos-23.11\";\n"
"  pkgs = import nixpkgs { config = {}; overlays = []; };\n"
"in\n"
"\n"
"pkgs.mkShellNoCC {\n"
"  packages = with pkgs; [\n"
"    hello\n"
"  ];\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/direnv.md:24
msgid "From the top-level directory of your project, run:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/direnv.md:26
msgid "$ echo \"use nix\" > .envrc && direnv allow\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/direnv.md:30
msgid ""
"The next time you launch your terminal and enter the top-level directory of "
"your project, `direnv` will automatically launch the shell defined in `shell."
"nix`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/direnv.md:32
msgid ""
"$ cd myproject\n"
"$ which hello\n"
"/nix/store/1gxz5nfzfnhyxjdyzi04r86sh61y4i00-hello-2.12.1/bin/hello\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/direnv.md:38
msgid "`direnv` will also check for changes to the `shell.nix` file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/direnv.md:40
msgid "Make the following addition:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/direnv.md:42
msgid ""
" let\n"
"   nixpkgs = fetchTarball \"https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/tarball/"
"nixos-23.11\";\n"
"   pkgs = import nixpkgs { config = {}; overlays = []; };\n"
" in\n"
"\n"
" pkgs.mkShellNoCC {\n"
"   packages = with pkgs; [\n"
"     hello\n"
"   ];\n"
"+\n"
"+  shellHook = ''\n"
"+    hello\n"
"+  '';\n"
" }\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/direnv.md:59
msgid ""
"The running environment should reload itself after the first interaction "
"(run any command or press `Enter`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/direnv.md:61
msgid "Hello, world!\n"
msgstr ""
